emory]", "task_id": "advisor-operator-recommendations-0074"}
{"escalations": {"t1+t3": {"model": "nvidia/nemotron-3-ultra-550b-a55b", "output": "Orionfold Arena is the cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local models with a leaderboard. The retrieved context states that \"Orionfold Arena is a single-screen cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local language models on one NVIDIA DGX Spark\" and shows \"a leaderboard built from your own results.\" The spec further separates concerns: Advisor is the flagship model product, while Workbench (which includes Arena, fieldkit, Cortex, and lane/eval/training receipts) is the build/govern/operate environment that creates and proves artifacts like Advisor. This indicates scoring/evaluation concerns (Arena) are kept separate from the training/export evidence that Advisor may cite. Citations: [product_orionfold_arena, spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1, spec_index]", "score": {"citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1", "spec_index"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "status": "ok", "tier": "T3", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 591, "cost": null, "prompt_tokens": 1772}}, "t1+t4": {"model": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5", "output": "Based on the retrieved public context:\n\n**Orionfold Arena** is the cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local models with a leaderboard. According to the product description, \"Orionfold Arena is a single-screen cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local language models on one NVIDIA DGX Spark,\" displaying GPU telemetry, published models, benchmark measurements, and a leaderboard built from your own results.\n\nRegarding separation of concerns: Yes, scoring should stay separate from training/export evidence. The retrieved context establishes this architectural principle explicitly: \"**Advisor** is the flagship model product\" while \"**Workbench** is the build/govern/operate environment that creates and proves artifacts.\" The Workbench integrates \"Arena + fieldkit + Cortex + lane/eval/training receipts\" as distinct operational layers. Training/export evidence (like NeMo Framework field notes documenting training performance) belongs in the training/export receipt layer, while Arena handles the evaluation and scoring cockpit function on the local machine.\n\nCitations: [product_orionfold_arena, spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1]", "score": {"citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "status": "ok", "tier": "T4", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 261, "cost": 0.003251, "prompt_tokens": 1946}}}, "expected_behavior": "answer", "family": "unsloth_arena_partner_path", "retrieval_top1_score": 45.003251, "retrieval_top1_source": "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1", "route": {"escalate": true, "hosted_egress_blocked": false, "private_state_query": false, "trigger": "citation_rank_sanity"}, "routed_t1+t3": {"citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1", "spec_index"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "routed_t1+t4": {"citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_orionfold_local_ai_workbench_v1"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "routed_t1-only": {"citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_index"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "t1": {"citation_ok": true, "cited_source_ids": ["product_orionfold_arena", "spec_index"], "passed": true, "private_state_risk": false, "refusal_ok": true, "route_ok": true, "thinking_leak": false}, "t1_output": "The Orionfold product that serves as the cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local models with a leaderboard is **Orionfold Arena**. According to the retrieved context, Orionfold Arena is described as \u201ca single\u2011screen cockpit for running, comparing, and scoring local language models on one NVIDIA DGX Spark,\u201d providing live telemetry, published models, benchmarks, and a leaderboard that stays on\u2011device. The question of whether scoring concerns should stay separate from training/export evidence is supported by the specification that separates **Arena + fieldkit + Cortex + lane/eval/training receipts** as the local AI Workbench product track, indicating that scoring (evaluation) is intentionally kept distinct from the training/export pipeline.  \n\nCitations: [product_orionfold_arena, spec_index]", "task_id": "advisor-unsloth-arena-partner-path-0082"}
